{
  "question_id": "54d1868a-36f3-4e8f-a8fd-f1010c0cd89e",
  "short_text": "Numbers in Hollow Square",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print a **Hollow Square** of `N` rows and `N` columns using numbers starting from **1**.\n\n```\n1 2 3\n1   3\n1 2 3\n```\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nThere is a space after every number.\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `N` rows and `N` columns containing numbers starting from **1** as a **Hollow Square** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 4`,\n\n- Print the numbers on **4** rows and **4** columns as shown in the given image.\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-numbers-in-hollow-square.png' widthPercent='70'/>\n\n<MultiLineNote>\n\nIn the given image,\n\n- The Empty box indicates two spaces (\"&nbsp;&nbsp;\").\n- The Number in the box indicates the number and a space (\"1 \").\n\n</MultiLineNote>\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n1 2 3 4\n1     4\n1     4\n1 2 3 4\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "3f1aa6f8-8b8d-4619-9341-733af5d8c8ec",
      "code_content": "rows = int(input())\n\nfor row in range(1, rows+1):\n    each_row = \"\"\n\n    for column in range(1, rows+1):\n        if row == 1 or row == rows:\n            each_row = each_row + str(column) + \" \"\n        else:\n            if column == 1 or column == rows:\n                each_row = each_row + str(column) + \" \"\n            else:\n                each_row = each_row + \"  \"\n    \n    print(each_row)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
